We are giving cash scholarships away

00:36:42.200 --> 00:36:43.701 line:95%,end
to further your education.

00:36:44.135 --> 00:36:47.638 line:95%,end
And this was decided upon
by the entire faculty.

00:36:48.105 --> 00:36:52.577 line:95%,end
Our junior winner is
Miss Maddie Ziegler.

00:36:52.643 --> 00:36:56.781 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:36:57.715 --> 00:37:00.818 line:95%,end
This will go to who the faculty feels

00:37:00.885 --> 00:37:02.853 line:95%,end
is the most improved student


00:37:02.920 --> 00:37:06.490 line:95%,end
in the Abby Lee Dance Company
for the 2012 season.

00:37:06.557 --> 00:37:08.459 line:95%,end
Miss Nia Frazier.

00:37:08.526 --> 00:37:12.163 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:37:14.532 --> 00:37:18.970 line:5%,start
I am so happy that Nia won
the Most Improved scholarship.

00:37:19.036 --> 00:37:21.672 line:95%,end
<i>This--this is wonderful for her.</i>

00:37:21.739 --> 00:37:23.774 line:95%,end
<i>This is a moment we have</i>
<i>all been waiting for,</i>

00:37:23.841 --> 00:37:27.011 line:95%,end
that Abby finally recognizes
what I've seen all along.

00:37:27.078 --> 00:37:28.246 line:95%,end
ABBY:
Thank you all for coming.

00:37:28.312 --> 00:37:29.780 line:95%,end
We will see you outside.

00:37:29.847 --> 00:37:31.082 line:95%,end
Thank you.

00:37:31.148 --> 00:37:34.719 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:37:34.785 --> 00:37:37.355 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:37:38.422 --> 00:37:41.459 line:95%,end
We cap off the evening
with a beautiful soiree

00:37:41.525 --> 00:37:43.060 line:95%,end
out on the veranda.

00:37:43.127 --> 00:37:46.097 line:95%,end
And this is a highlight
of the dance concert.

00:37:47.164 --> 00:37:49.100 line:5%,start
Hey, how you doing?

00:37:50.167 --> 00:37:53.571 line:5%,start
I was very nervous about
meeting with these alumni.

00:37:53.638 --> 00:37:56.507 line:5%,start
I thought, "Oh God, I'm not even
going to recognize them."

00:37:56.574 --> 00:37:59.110 line:95%,end
<i>You know, but I really</i>
<i>had a good time.</i>

00:37:59.176 --> 00:38:00.378 line:95%,end
Thank you.
You were here last year, too.

00:38:00.444 --> 00:38:01.579 line:95%,end
KELLY:
Abby, I need to know,

00:38:01.646 --> 00:38:04.682 line:95%,end
did the alumni talk
any bad stuff on me?

00:38:04.749 --> 00:38:06.350 line:95%,end
I haven't talked to the alumni yet.

00:38:06.417 --> 00:38:07.451 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:38:07.518 --> 00:38:09.487 line:95%,end
Had it been under different
circumstances,

00:38:09.553 --> 00:38:13.024 line:95%,end
I'm sure that every one of those alumni

00:38:13.090 --> 00:38:15.192 line:95%,end
would have had a story about Kelly

00:38:15.259 --> 00:38:16.794 line:95%,end
and how much they hate her.

00:38:16.861 --> 00:38:18.329 line:95%,end
Was Kelly ever late?

00:38:18.396 --> 00:38:19.864 line:95%,end
ALL: Yes!

00:38:19.930 --> 00:38:21.632 line:95%,end
Did Kelly ever not show up?

00:38:21.699 --> 00:38:22.700 line:95%,end
ALL: Yes!

00:38:22.767 --> 00:38:24.468 line:95%,end
Was Kelly naked all the time?

00:38:24.535 --> 00:38:25.436 line:95%,end
ALL: Yes!

00:38:25.503 --> 00:38:26.504 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:38:26.570 --> 00:38:27.972 line:95%,end
(chuckling)

00:38:28.039 --> 00:38:29.206 line:95%,end
Is Kelly fun?

00:38:29.273 --> 00:38:30.775 line:95%,end
(crickets)

00:38:30.841 --> 00:38:33.044 line:95%,end
(chuckling)

00:38:33.110 --> 00:38:35.146 line:95%,end
Is that woman delusional or what?

00:38:35.212 --> 00:38:36.747 line:95%,end
-Hi, nice to meet you.
-Hi.

00:38:36.814 --> 00:38:37.982 line:5%,start
-Miss Miller?
-ABBY: Yes.

00:38:38.049 --> 00:38:39.850 line:5%,start
-This is Nicaya.
-Hi.

00:38:39.917 --> 00:38:41.185 line:95%,end
Nice to meet you, sweetie.

00:38:41.252 --> 00:38:43.621 line:95%,end
We're looking for a new
studio to compete.

00:38:43.688 --> 00:38:45.222 line:95%,end
-Where are you from?
-St. Louis.

00:38:45.289 --> 00:38:46.190 line:95%,end
St. Louis?

00:38:46.257 --> 00:38:49.226 line:95%,end
KAYA: I think Nicaya has something
to offer your team.

00:38:49.293 --> 00:38:51.996 line:95%,end
Okay. We're having a little
workshop in the studio.

00:38:52.063 --> 00:38:54.031 line:95%,end
-Mm-hmm.
-So why don't you come?

00:38:54.665 --> 00:38:56.667 line:95%,end
You can come take a little
tour of the studio,

00:38:56.734 --> 00:38:59.036 line:95%,end
and she can take class,
and I can observe her during class.

00:38:59.103 --> 00:39:01.072 line:95%,end
So do you have room
on your competition team?

00:39:01.138 --> 00:39:02.373 line:95%,end
I always have room.

00:39:02.440 --> 00:39:03.641 line:95%,end
There's never enough students.

00:39:03.708 --> 00:39:05.509 line:95%,end
It's been an outstanding show.

00:39:05.976 --> 00:39:10.514 line:95%,end
And now I want to sit back and relax
and enjoy my evening,

00:39:10.581 --> 00:39:15.953 line:95%,end
when all of a sudden
I hear this agitating grating voice.

00:39:16.020 --> 00:39:17.955 line:95%,end
We, you know, groom you

00:39:18.022 --> 00:39:19.957 line:95%,end
into becoming part
of our competition team.

00:39:20.024 --> 00:39:22.760 line:95%,end
I'm footing the bill for this,
and she was not invited.

00:39:22.827 --> 00:39:27.031 line:95%,end
All I know is she has no
business being anywhere

00:39:27.098 --> 00:39:28.366 line:95%,end
near my customers.

00:39:28.432 --> 00:39:30.668 line:95%,end
Technically her dancers were amazing.

00:39:30.735 --> 00:39:32.470 line:95%,end
But did you feel that, like,

00:39:32.536 --> 00:39:34.372 line:95%,end
the steps were somewhat limited?

00:39:34.438 --> 00:39:36.707 line:95%,end
Like, not a whole lot of choreography
going on?

00:39:36.774 --> 00:39:38.042 line:95%,end
You know what, I need to tell you,

00:39:38.109 --> 00:39:40.578 line:95%,end
you sound like you would
make a dandy Apple.

00:39:40.644 --> 00:39:42.246 line:95%,end
-Yeah, she would.
-(laughter)

00:39:42.313 --> 00:39:44.081 line:95%,end
We're a little wilted

00:39:44.148 --> 00:39:46.984 line:95%,end
because there wasn't a whole
lot of air conditioning--

00:39:47.051 --> 00:39:48.486 line:95%,end
There was air conditioning.

00:39:48.552 --> 00:39:50.454 line:95%,end
There was just a lot of hot air.

00:39:50.521 --> 00:39:51.722 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:39:51.789 --> 00:39:55.960 line:95%,end
Thank you so much for having us
invited to this lovely show.

00:39:56.026 --> 00:39:57.595 line:95%,end
-I didn't know you were invited.
-I have--

00:39:57.661 --> 00:39:59.029 line:95%,end
Yes, you invited us.

00:39:59.096 --> 00:40:00.798 line:95%,end
We got tickets from you.

00:40:00.865 --> 00:40:01.899 line:95%,end
Not from me.

00:40:01.966 --> 00:40:03.501 line:95%,end
How did she get here?

00:40:03.567 --> 00:40:04.869 line:95%,end
I don't see a broom in sight.

00:40:04.935 --> 00:40:05.903 line:95%,end
No backdrops.

00:40:05.970 --> 00:40:07.538 line:95%,end
-Black curtain.
-No.

00:40:07.605 --> 00:40:08.873 line:95%,end
No money on your end?

00:40:08.939 --> 00:40:10.674 line:95%,end
Come on, you gotta step it up.

00:40:10.741 --> 00:40:13.677 line:95%,end
Did she fly in?
Who knows?

00:40:13.744 --> 00:40:14.812 line:95%,end
-We have the (indistinct)
-JILL: Aren't you glad guys

00:40:14.879 --> 00:40:16.847 line:95%,end
-I invited Cathy?
-And we have (indistinct)

00:40:16.914 --> 00:40:18.616 line:95%,end
Aren't you glad guys
I invited everybody in?

00:40:18.682 --> 00:40:20.384 line:95%,end
And they're--and they're all--
and they're all--

00:40:20.451 --> 00:40:23.921 line:95%,end
Listen! Listen, she's the one
that invited us.

00:40:23.988 --> 00:40:25.322 line:95%,end
<i>I invited Cathy</i>

00:40:25.389 --> 00:40:28.125 line:5%,start
because I wanted her to see
how Kendall fits in

00:40:28.192 --> 00:40:29.193 line:5%,start
with this team.

00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:31.796 line:5%,start
-Oh, Jill invited you.
-I invited them.

00:40:31.862 --> 00:40:33.931 line:5%,start
I wanted them to see
what we've all been up to.

00:40:33.998 --> 00:40:35.166 line:5%,start
CATHY:
Your tickets are paper.

00:40:35.232 --> 00:40:37.301 line:5%,start
Jill, use your brain.

00:40:37.368 --> 00:40:38.636 line:5%,start
<i>Why would she bring</i>

00:40:38.702 --> 00:40:40.971 line:5%,start
<i>my arch rival enemy</i>

00:40:41.038 --> 00:40:43.374 line:5%,start
in to my own show?

00:40:43.441 --> 00:40:44.875 line:5%,start
To steal my ideas?

00:40:44.942 --> 00:40:46.110 line:5%,start
To steal your music?

00:40:46.177 --> 00:40:49.013 line:5%,start
We only saw five minutes of your show,
and that was enough,

00:40:49.079 --> 00:40:50.948 line:5%,start
so--but thanks for the great reception.

00:40:51.015 --> 00:40:52.016 line:5%,start
ABBY: You're welcome.

00:40:52.082 --> 00:40:53.617 line:5%,start
Don't let the door hit your
(bleep) on the way out.

00:40:53.684 --> 00:40:55.119 line:5%,start
Oh, honey, you can't afford a door.

00:40:55.186 --> 00:40:56.387 line:5%,start
That's the problem.

